          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">
     Trump hosts Netanyahu
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/netanyahu-praises-trump-peace-efforts-gaza-ceasefire-talks.jpg" alt="Netanyahu was quick to burnish Trump’s peace-making abilities, even as negotiators were still finalizing details of a ceasefire deal" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>
          Netanyahu was quick to burnish Trump’s peace-making abilities, even as negotiators were still finalizing details of a ceasefire agreement. Credits: AP Photo/Alex Brandon</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
       At a dinner hosted at the White House, Israeli PM Benjamin Netanyahu gave Donald Trump a formal letter nominating him for the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #102341; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-8-jul-25-spotlight-h1-1-nobel-peace-prize" target="_blank">Nobel Peace Prize</a>. He praised Trump’s role in promoting peace, especially his efforts to end the war between Israel and Hamas.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
    Negotiators from both sides are currently in Qatar discussing a possible 60-day truce. The US is also under growing pressure to help end the conflict, with the intention of expanding the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #102341; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-8-jul-25-spotlight-h1-2-abraham-accords" target="_blank">Abraham Accords</a> (a set of agreements normalizing relations between Israel and several Arab states).</p>
         <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
     Trump has become increasingly focused on bagging the Nobel Peace Prize. He believes his work on international diplomacy, especially in the Middle East, has been unrecognized. Ending the Gaza war would strengthen that claim and help shape his legacy. To achieve this, Trump sees Netanyahu as a crucial ally despite the tensions. </p>
    <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
    Track the ceasefire efforts <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #102341; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-8-jul-25-spotlight-h1-3-here" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
