       <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-top:4px;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>🇷🇺 Russia - Ex-Minister commits suicide.</strong> 
           Former Russian Transport Minister Roman Starovoit committed suicide hours after being dismissed by President Putin. He was found with a gunshot wound in his car near Moscow. Reports suggest he was facing arrest over alleged embezzlement related to fortifications in Kursk. His dismissal coincided with major air travel disruptions across Russia (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #102341; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-8-jul-25-worldwide-12-russian-house-of-cards" target="_blank">Russian House of Cards</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>🇺🇲 USA - Trump seeks additional tariffs.</strong> 
          Donald Trump warned of a 10% additional tariff on countries that align with BRICS policies, which conflict with the US interests. The threat follows the failure of trade agreement deadlines, with updated tariffs set to take effect on August 1. The US has struck trade agreements with the UK and Vietnam, as well as a partial agreement with China (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #102341; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-8-jul-25-worldwide-13-tariff-uncertainty" target="_blank">tariff uncertainty</a>). 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>🇨🇳 China - Warning to EU.</strong> 
          China’s FM Wang Yi reportedly told the EU that Beijing cannot accept a Russian defeat in Ukraine, fearing increased US focus on China. Despite public neutrality, China’s deepening ties with Russia and alleged drone component support suggest strategic alignment (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #102341; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-8-jul-25-worldwide-14-china-eu-tension" target="_blank">China-EU tension</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
          <strong>🇰🇪 Kenya - Demonstrators killed.</strong> 
          Two protesters were reportedly shot dead in Nairobi during Saba Saba Day demonstrations. Police fired tear gas and blocked key roads amid the anti-government protests demanding accountability and an end to police brutality. Activists accuse police of colluding with violent groups, while calls for government-youth dialogue grow amid continued unrest (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #102341; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-8-jul-25-worldwide-15-kenyan-unrest" target="_blank">Kenyan unrest</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
          <strong>🇮🇶 Iraq - Gas poisoning kills soldiers.</strong> 
          Turkey reported that 12 soldiers died from methane gas poisoning during a cave search operation in northern Iraq. The operation aimed to find a soldier killed by Kurdish fighters. It exposed 19 soldiers to gas in a cave used by the Kurdish Workers Party (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #102341; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-8-jul-25-worldwide-16-about-the-incident" target="_blank">about the incident</a>). 
          </p>
        </mj-text>
